[All from Public Health Services, Ministry of Health, Jerusalem, Israel]

[A reliable source has informed us that several sheep, goats, rabbits, guinea pigs, and 3 ponies were kept on the petting zoo; only the ponies are still there. It will be of interest to note where the other animals are currently being kept and if they have been sampled before movement. The Nir-Oz Kibbutz also maintains a large beef-cattle feedlot.

Without further evidence, considering the petting zoo as the source of infection remains a "suggestion", as rightly commented by the authors - Mod.AS]

[Maps of Israel can be seen at http://www.eyeonisrael.com/Israel-touring-map.html and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4201599,53099. Nir Oz can be located on the map at http://www.weather-forecast.com/place_maps/ni/Nir-Oz.8.gif. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
